'''Madhurai Perumaruthanār''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: மதுரைப் பெருமருதனார்) was a poet of the [[Sangam period]], to whom a single verse of the Sangam literature has been attributed, besides verse 37 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai">{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title = திருவள்ளுவ மாலை மூலமும் எளிய உரை விளக்கமும் [Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum] | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages =52–53 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Madurai Perumarudhanar hailed from the city of [[Madurai]]. He is the father of the Sangam poet [[Madurai Perumarudhu Ilanaganar]].<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai"/>
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Madurai Perumarudhanar has written a sole Sangam verse—verse 241 of the [[Natrinai]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_1">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = நற்றிணை, ஐங்குறுநூறு [Natrinai, Ainkurunuru] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 1 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 247 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> Apart from this, he has also composed verse 37 in the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai"/>
