{{Use DMY dates|date=October 2017}} {{Vietnamese name|[[Phạm]]|Nguyên}} {{Infobox person | name = Phạm Xuân Nguyên | other_names = Ngân Xuyên (pen name) | image = File:Nhà lý luận phê bình văn học Phạm Xuân Nguyên.jpg | caption = Nguyên speaking at an event held by the Center for East-West Cultures and Languages ''(Trung tâm văn hoá ngôn ngữ Đông Tây)'', 4 December 2008 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1958|5|15|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Nghệ An Province]] | nationality = [[Vietnam]]ese | occupation = Writer and [[literary translator]] | known_for = Vietnamese translations of the works of [[Georges Bataille]], [[Paulo Coelho]], [[Jhumpa Lahiri]], [[Milan Kundera]], [[Haruki Murakami]], and others }}
'''Phạm Xuân Nguyên''' (born 15 May 1958), better known by his [[pen name]] '''Ngân Xuyên''', is a [[Vietnamese literature|Vietnamese writer]] and [[literary translation|literary translator]].<ref name="TN20100329">{{cite news|url=http://www.thanhnien.com.vn/van-hoa-nghe-thuat/chang-emxi-chuyen-dan-dat-cac-so-van-chuong-328294.html|author=Nguyễn Việt Chiến|title=Chàng 'em-xi' chuyên dẫn dắt các 'sô' văn chương|work=[[Thanh Niên]]|date=29 March 2010|accessdate=28 August 2015}}</ref>
==Personal life and career== Phạm Xuân Nguyên was born in [[Nghệ An Province]].<ref name="TN20100329"/> He did his early education in neighbouring [[Hà Tĩnh Province]], where in grade 6 and again in grade 10 he won district and provincial awards for writing.<ref name="NDT20121227">{{cite news|url=http://www.nguoiduatin.vn/chuyen-ve-nha-phe-binh-dat-so-nhat-viet-nam-a59127.html|author=Thanh Xuân|title=Chuyện về nhà phê bình 'đắt sô' nhất Việt Nam|work=Người đưa tin|date=27 December 2012|accessdate=28 August 2015}}</ref> He studied [[Russian language|Russian]] as his foreign language in high school, and continued learning it as a student in the literature department of the [[University of Hanoi]] (''[[:vi:Trường Đại học Tổng hợp Hà Nội|Trường Đại học Tổng hợp Hà Nội]]'', now part of the [[Vietnam National University, Hanoi]]).<ref name="ANTGCT20131205">{{cite news|url=http://antgct.cand.com.vn/Chuyen-de/Nguyen-van-la-Nguyen-315599/|title= Nhà phê bình văn học Phạm Xuân Nguyên, Chủ tịch Hội Nhà văn Hà Nội: 'Nguyên vẫn là Nguyên'|work=An ninh thế giới Cuối tháng|date=5 December 2013|accessdate=28 August 2015}}</ref> He interrupted his university studies to serve in the [[People's Army of Vietnam]] from 1978 to 1982, and was stationed in [[Ho Chi Minh City]]. During that period, he began teaching himself [[French language|French]], and had his first translations of [[French poetry]] published in the newspaper ''[[Tiền Phong (newspaper)|Tiền Phong]]''.<ref name="NDT20121227"/> He went on to become chairman of the Hanoi Writers' Association ''(Hội Nhà văn Hà Nội)''.<ref name="ANTGCT20131205"/>
==Works== Phạm Xuân Nguyên speaks Russian, French, and English, and has translated works from all of those languages into Vietnamese.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thanhnien.com.vn/van-hoa-nghe-thuat/pham-xuan-nguyen-lam-gi-cung-phai-co-trach-nhiem-va-chat-luong-cao-nhat-co-the-20596.html|author=Ngô Thị Kim Cúc|title=Phạm Xuân Nguyên: Làm gì cũng phải có trách nhiệm và chất lượng cao nhất có thể|work=[[Thanh Niên]]|date=30 July 2013|accessdate=27 August 2015}}</ref> He was first exposed to the works of [[Milan Kundera]] in their Russian translations in the [[Union of Russian Writers]] journal ''Foreign Literature'' («[[:ru:Иностранная литература|Иностранная литература]]»), and himself translated ''[[Immortality (novel)|Immortality]]'' (which was originally in [[Czech language|Czech]]) into Vietnamese from the Russian version.<ref name="ANTGCT20131205"/>
After he spent more than thirty years translating the works of others under his pen name, his first book of his own under his real name, ''Nhà văn như Thị Nở'' (meaning "A Writer like Thị Nở"), was published in 2014.<ref name="VNExpress">{{cite news|url=http://giaitri.vnexpress.net/tin-tuc/sach/lang-van/bien-tap-vien-doa-dot-nha-de-co-ban-thao-cua-pham-xuan-nguyen-3008642.html|title=Biên tập viên dọa đốt nhà để có bản thảo của Phạm Xuân Nguyên|trans-title=Editor threatened to commit arson to get Phạm Xuân Nguyên's draft|work=VNExpress|date=25 June 2014|accessdate=27 August 2015}}</ref> The title is a reference to the character Thị Nở in [[Nam Cao]]'s 1941 short story ''[[Chí Phèo]]'', a woman who is well known for her unattractive appearance.<ref name="DSPL20140731">{{cite news|url=http://www.doisongphapluat.com/giai-tri/nghe-ga-dau-bac-pham-xuan-nguyen-ke-toi-thi-no-a43698.html|author=Lạc Thành|title=Nghe 'gã đầu bạc' Phạm Xuân Nguyên 'kể tội'... Thị Nở|trans-title=Hear 'the white-haired man' Phạm Xuân Nguyên 'tell all' ... Thị Nở|work=Báo Đời Sống Pháp Luật|date=31 July 2014|accessdate=30 August 2015}}</ref> ''Nhà văn như Thị Nở'' is a collection of essays of [[literary criticism]], discussing fifty-one Vietnamese writers including [[Nam Trân]], [[Thế Lữ]], [[Hải Triều]], [[Hoài Thanh]], [[Nguyễn Tuân]], [[Trương Tửu]], [[Bích Khê]], [[Xuân Diệu]], [[Tố Hữu]], [[Nguyễn Huy Tưởng]], [[Nguyễn Hữu Đang]], [[Hoàng Cầm (poet)|Hoàng Cầm]], [[Trần Dần]], [[Lê Đạt]], [[Phùng Quán]], [[Bùi Ngọc Tấn]], [[Nguyễn Xuân Khánh]], [[Dương Tường]], [[Bảo Ninh]], [[Nguyễn Quang Lập]], and [[Vi Thùy Linh]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://vanhien.vn/vi/news/sach/Nha-phe-binh-Pham-Xuan-Nguyen-Nha-van-nhu-Thi-No-6672/|author=Vũ Gia Hà|title=Nhà phê bình Phạm Xuân Nguyên: Nhà văn như Thị Nở|trans-title=Critic Phạm Xuân Nguyên: A Writer like Thị Nở|work=Văn Hiến Việt Nam|date=15 May 2014|accessdate=28 August 2015}}</ref> Nguyên stated that it took him so long to come out with the book because he was too lazy to collect his previous essays and edit them into a coherent whole; in particular, he mentioned the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification|World Cup season]] as one of the various reasons for his delays in submitting the final version to the publisher Nhã Nam for printing.<ref name="DSPL20140731"/> Editor Diệu Thủy stated that the whole process took more than four years, and that at one time she even jokingly threatened to burn down Nguyên's house in an effort to get him to submit a draft.<ref name="VNExpress"/><ref name="DSPL20140731"/>
